                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/5093: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Munro</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-10-29T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 29, 1927—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>173. Your 289, October 24, 3 p.m. Department concurs with you that it would be
                    better to follow the suggestion of Minister of Foreign Affairs and have Supreme
                    Court elect General McCoy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Olds</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
